{"id":26870161954,"name":"Test","node_id":"WFR_kwLOA_1uaM8AAAAGQZYiIg","head_branch":"perf/users-perf-test-isolate-scenarios","head_sha":"e94f93f40d3c43a2825bb21ac9a6558dd2279863","path":".github/workflows/run-tests.yml","run_number":53949,"run_attempt":1,"event":"pull_request","display_title":"perf: isolate UsersPerformanceTest scenarios and reuse session","status":"completed","conclusion":"success","workflow_id":10954,"check_suite_id":72089466524,"check_suite_node_id":"CS_kwDOA_1uaM8AAAAQyN32nA","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/26870161954","html_url":"https://github.com/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/26870161954","pull_requests":[{"id":3793441996,"number":24107,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/pulls/24107","head":{"ref":"perf/users-perf-test-isolate-scenarios","sha":"e94f93f40d3c43a2825bb21ac9a6558dd2279863","repo":{"id":66940520,"name":"dhis2-core","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core"}},"base":{"ref":"master","sha":"5a1b89baf57c3f7563c2c12de21f5f9777b3d6b0","repo":{"id":66940520,"name":"dhis2-core","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core"}}}],"created_at":"2026-06-03T07:27:17Z","updated_at":"2026-06-03T07:58:38Z","run_started_at":"2026-06-03T07:27:17Z","jobs_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/26870161954/jobs","logs_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/26870161954/logs","check_suite_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/check-suites/72089466524","artifacts_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/26870161954/artifacts","cancel_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/26870161954/cancel","rerun_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/26870161954/rerun","head_commit":{"message":"perf: isolate UsersPerformanceTest scenarios and reuse session\n\nThe \"GET User - by uid\" p95 assertion kept failing on CI (e.g. 783ms vs\n700ms) while the endpoint is ~10-24ms in isolation. The latency was an\nartifact of how the test measured, not the endpoint:\n\n1. Parallel mode (primary). Default mode=parallel ran all 7 scenarios\n   concurrently, and on the single shared self-hosted CI runner the\n   bcrypt-heavy write scenarios (password hashing on POST/PUT/REPLICA\n   payloads, plus per-virtual-user login) saturated CPU and stretched the\n   GET tail. Running scenarios sequentially takes GET p95 from 783ms on CI\n   to ~24ms in isolation. Faster multi-core dev machines hide the\n   contention entirely, which is why it never reproduced locally.\n\n2. One-time auth bcrypt charged to the first measured request (secondary).\n   DHIS2 is stateful (SessionCreationPolicy.IF_REQUIRED +\n   HttpSessionSecurityContextRepository), so with the default cookie jar\n   the session is reused and bcrypt is paid only once per virtual user --\n   but with protocol-level basicAuth that one-time ~90ms cost landed inside\n   the first GET/POST/... request and surfaced in their p95/max (e.g. POST\n   p95 172ms -\u003e 103ms once isolated). There is NO per-request bcrypt and no\n   missing auth cache; this is expected Spring Security behaviour.\n\n3. Tiny sample size made p95 a coin flip (~10-20 samples/scenario).\n\nChanges:\n- Default mode to sequential so each scenario is measured in isolation.\n  parallel remains available as an opt-in mixed-load stress mode.\n- Authenticate once per virtual user via a separately-named request and\n  reuse the JSESSIONID cookie, so the one-time auth bcrypt is excluded from\n  the per-endpoint assertions. Relies on CSRF being disabled (DHIS2\n  default) so session-cookie writes are accepted.\n- Bump iterations (load 10-\u003e30, smoke 3-\u003e10) for a more stable p95.\n\nVerified locally (sequential): GET p50 ~11ms, p95 ~19-24ms; all write\nscenarios succeed under session-cookie auth.\n\nThresholds were calibrated under the old parallel regime and are now far\ntoo loose; they are flagged in-code as pending recalibration from fresh\nnightly baselines.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e","author":{"name":"Jason Pickering","email":"jason@dhis2.org"},"id":"e94f93f40d3c43a2825bb21ac9a6558dd2279863","tree_id":"da73d00fa497d7ef570c2305d8affa3c69a4268d","timestamp":"2026-06-03T07:27:09Z","committer":{"name":"Jason Pickering","email":"jason@dhis2.org"}},"workflow_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/workflows/10954","repository":{"id":66940520,"node_id":"MDEwOlJlcG9zaXRvcnk2Njk0MDUyMA==","owner":{"login":"dhis2","id":1089987,"node_id":"MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjEwODk5ODc=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1089987?v=4","html_url":"https://github.com/dhis2","gravatar_id":"","type":"Organization","site_admin":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/events{/privacy}","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/following{/other_user}","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/followers","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/gists{/gist_id}","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/orgs","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/received_events","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/repos","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/subscriptions"},"name":"dhis2-core","full_name":"dhis2/dhis2-core","description":"DHIS 2 Core. Written in Java. Contains the service layer and Web API.","html_url":"https://github.com/dhis2/dhis2-core","fork":false,"private":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core","archive_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/{archive_format}{/ref}","assignees_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/assignees{/user}","blobs_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/git/blobs{/sha}","branches_url":"https://api.github.c